      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The primary QoI (normalized index of hemolysis, NIH) must be directly traceable to the clinical endpoint (plasma free hemoglobin) through a validated power-law hemolysis model. Secondary QoIs (wall shear stress, exposure time) must be documented as inputs to the hemolysis model.",
      "rationale": "NIH computed from the Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law model applied to Lagrangian particle trajectories. Direct mapping from NIH to plasma free hemoglobin established via published calibration. Wall shear stress and scalar exposure time documented as intermediate QoIs feeding the hemolysis model."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
