      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments must be conducted on the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump geometry at flow conditions overlapping the COU operating envelope (2–8 L/min, 2500–3500 RPM). At least three of five COU operating points must be directly validated.",
      "rationale": "Validation performed on FDA generic centrifugal pump at five operating points spanning 2.5–7 L/min and 2000–3500 RPM. Four of five COU operating points fall within the validated envelope. Experimental data sourced from FDA CDRH published benchmark dataset."
